// Boltrope orchestrator wire contract (the client-facing edge).
//
// OrchestratorService is the system's only "brain": it runs the gather -> act ->
// verify agent loop, drives turns, enforces permissions and hooks, manages the
// context/token budget, spawns depth-limited sub-agents, and persists/replays the
// event-sourced log to PostgreSQL via an in-process package. This proto is the
// client (CLI/IDE/CI/SDK) -> orchestrator boundary; a REST/JSON facade is added
// later over these same definitions, via google.api.http annotations and a
// buf.build/googleapis/googleapis dependency, generated by a grpc-gateway plugin
// wired into buf.gen.yaml at that time. No such annotations exist yet
// (architecture 4.1, spec 7.1).
//
// Resumability is first-class: Run server-streams EventFrames each carrying a
// per-session seq (a Last-Event-ID); a reconnecting client resumes via after_seq
// on Run or via Control.Reattach, receiving only events with seq greater than the
// supplied value (spec 7.1, FR-API-01/02).

